ensities. A fairly flat distribution in ionization parameter is necessary to\nexplain the inferred radial ionic column densities of all spectra. This must\nprimarily be due to a broad density distribution at each radius, spanning\nroughly 0.1-100 cm$^{-3}$. (Abridged)\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sat, 2 Mar 2002 01:53:27 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 6 Mar 2002 17:57:53 GMT"}],"update_date":"2007-05-23"}
